<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>
<p>
Facts about the <a knowl="def/vec/tensor-product">tensor product</a>.
</p>
<ul>
<li>
The tensor product is commutative:
\(V\otimes W\simeq W\otimes V\).
<details>
<summary>
[explanation]
</summary>
Define a bilinear map \(\varphi:V\times W\to W\otimes V\) via
\((v, w)\mapsto w\otimes v\). By the universal property of the tensor
product, there exists a unique linear map
\[\widetilde\varphi:V\otimes W\to W\otimes V.\]
Similarly, define a bilinear map \(\psi:W\times V\to V\otimes W\)
via \((w, v)\mapsto v\otimes w\). By the universal property of the 
tensor product, there exists a unique linear map
\[\widetilde\psi:W\otimes V\to V\otimes W.\]
These maps are clear inverses of each other,
which means that \(V\otimes W\) and \(W\otimes V\) are isomorphic.
</details>
</li>
<li>
The tensor product is associative:
\(A\otimes(B\otimes C)\simeq (A\otimes B)\otimes C\).
<details>
<summary>
[explanation]
</summary>
</details>
</li>
<li>
The \(\otimes\) functor is adjoint to the Hom functor:
\[\Hom(U\otimes V, W)\simeq\Hom(U,\Hom(V, W))\]
<details>
<summary>
[explanation]
</summary>
</details>
</li>
<li>
Tensor respects dual: \((U\otimes V)^*\simeq U^*\otimes V^*\).
<details>
<summary>
[explanation]
</summary>
</details>
</li>
<li>
\(\Hom(V, W)\simeq V^*\otimes W\).
<details>
<summary>
[explanation]
</summary>
\[
\begin{align*}
\Hom(V, W) &\simeq\Hom(V, W^{**})\\
&\simeq\Hom(V,\Hom(W^*, \mathbf F))\\
&\simeq\Hom(V\otimes W^*,\mathbf F)\\
&\simeq(V\otimes W^*)^*\\
&\simeq V^*\otimes W.
\end{align*}
\]
</details>
</li>
<li>
\(\Hom(U, V\otimes W)\simeq\Hom(U, V)\otimes W\).
<details>
<summary>
[explanation]
</summary>
\[
\begin{align*}
\Hom(U, V\otimes W) &\simeq U^*\otimes(V\otimes W)\\
&\simeq (U^*\otimes V)\otimes W\\
&\simeq \Hom(U, V)\otimes W.
\end{align*}
\]
</details>
</li>
<li>
\(\Hom(\Hom(U, V), W)\simeq U\otimes\Hom(V, W)\).
<details>
<summary>
[explanation]
</summary>
\[
\begin{align*}
\Hom(\Hom(U, V), W) &\simeq\Hom(U^*\otimes V, W)\\
&\simeq (U^*\otimes V)^*\otimes W\\
&\simeq (U\otimes V^*)\otimes W\\
&\simeq U\otimes(V^*\otimes W)\\
&\simeq U\otimes\Hom(V, W).
\end{align*}
\]
</details>
</li>
<li>
\(\Hom(A\otimes B, C\otimes D)\simeq\Hom(A, C)\otimes\Hom(B, D)\).
<details>
<summary>
[explanation]
</summary>
\[
\begin{align*}
\Hom(A\otimes B, C\otimes D) &\simeq\Hom(A,\Hom(B, C\otimes D))\\
&\simeq\Hom(A,\Hom(B, D\otimes C))\\
&\simeq\Hom(A,\Hom(B, D)\otimes C)\\
&\simeq\Hom(A, C\otimes\Hom(B, D))\\
&\simeq\Hom(A, C)\otimes\Hom(B, D).
\end{align*}
\]
</details>
</li>
</ul>
</body>
</html>
